<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mongolian Leader Visit Continues, Meetings Noted </TI></H3>
<H4>   Le Duc Anh Hosts Banquet </H4>
<F P=102> BK0503112794 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1430 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0503112794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Vietnamese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] SRV President Le Duc Anh today received Mongolian 
President Punsalmaagiyn Ochirbat and his entourage on their 
arrival in Hanoi. On behalf of the government and people of 
Vietnam, President Le Duc Anh warmly welcomed President 
Ochirbat, his wife, and other Mongolian guests now on a visit to 
Vietnam, bringing with them the age-old relations of friendship 
and solidarity between the two countries. 
  President Le Duc Anh held that this visit by the delegation 
would contribute to strengthening understanding and further 
consolidating the existing relationship between the two 
countries in conformity with the new situation at present. 
  On behalf of his delegation, President Ochirbat sincerely 
thanked President Le Duc Anh and the Vietnamese Government for 
having reserved a cordial and grand welcome for his delegation. 
He emphasized that this visit to Vietnam is a good opportunity 
for Mongolia to exchange experiences with Vietnam and learn from 
Vietnam's experience acquired during its renovation process and 
national construction. The president expressed his firm belief 
that the long-standing relations of friendship between Mongolia 
and Vietnam will continue to be consolidated and developed for 
the benefit of each respective country. 
  President Le Duc Anh and his wife hosted a banquet this 
evening for President Ochirbat, his wife, and their entourage. 
  At the banquet, together with all those in attendance, 
Presidents Le Duc Anh and Ochirbat proposed toasts to the 
increasing consolidation and growth of the long-standing 
relations of friendship and cooperation between the two 
countries and to the fine success of President Ochirbat's visit 
to Vietnam. 
  During the banquet, held at the presidential palace, 
President Ochirbat, his wife, and other Mongolian guests were 
treated to a unique art performance given in honor of their 
delegation. 

</TEXT>

